bio: [('Beginning', 'She began weightlifting at age 11 in Zamboanga, Philippines. (SportsDeskOnline, 07 Aug 2016)BUSINESS OWNERIn 2017 she opened a weightlifting gym in Zamboanga, Philippines. (definitelyfilipino.com, 28 Oct 2017)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralREPRESENTING THE PHILIPPINESShe was born in the Philippines to a Japanese father and Filipina mother. name: MARELLA VANIA
bio: [('Beginning', 'She took up cycling in 2013. (spin.ph, 11 Jun 2015)'), ('Reason', 'She was originally involved in tenpin bowling before she switched to cycling. She was advised by her bowling coaches to lose weight so she took up cycling as part of her training and also had a spell boxing. She was then scouted by national cycling coach Cesar Lobramonte. "I wanted to lose weight and I took up several sports, but it never entered my mind to become a full-time cyclist. But the moment I tried cycling, I enjoyed it. And now, cycling is in my system and won\'t let go." (businessmirror.com.ph, 11 Nov 2016; spin.ph, 11 Jun 2015)'), ('Coach', 'Cesar Lobramonte [national] (bworldonline.com, 12 Dec 2017)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (businessmirror.com.ph, 11 Nov 2016)'), ('Memorable', 'Winning the 2015 Tour of Subic in the Philippines, and winning a bronze medal at the 2016 World University Cycling Championships in Tagaytay City, Philippines. (businessmirror.com.ph, 11 Nov 2016)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralOLYMPIC FUNDINGIn March 2018 she was selected as one of 29 Filipino athletes to receive funding from the Siklab Atleta Pilipinas Sports Foundation. The foundation was set up to help the Philippines win their first gold medal at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (news.abs-cbn.com, 06 Mar 2018)BREAK IN EDUCATIONShe studied dentistry for a time at the University of the East [UE] in Manila, Philippines, before dropping out of her course during her second year. She initially took a break to focus on cycling before switching to online marketing course at Southville Foreign University in Las Pinas, Philippines. "It was a difficult decision to drop dentistry. But I wanted to train and compete, especially when the national team needs me. I have sacrificed a lot of things. My studies and also my time away from my family. I dreamt of representing the Philippines, and through cycling, all my sacrifices are worth it." (manilatimes.net, 24 Mar 2017; businessmirror.com.ph, 11 Nov 2016) '), ('Relatives', 'Her father Rodolfo has competed in tenpin bowling professionally. (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Debut', '2012 for Philippines (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Coach', 'Rene Herrera [national], PHI; John Philip Duenas [personal], PHI, from 2009 (pinoyathletics.info, 03 Dec 2017; Instagram profile, 09 Aug 2018)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. She dedicated the victory to her father Rolando, who passed away the day before the race. "It was a really trying time for me, but I had to be stronger. I was 100% ready to win. I finished strongly and safely because I know my Papa was there running with me. I know he wanted me to achieve my goal of becoming a five-time Milo Marathon Queen. I dedicate this race to my Papa. I know he will be with me in all of my races. He was the one who taught me to never give up, and I never will." (news.abs-cbn.com, 03 Dec 2017)OTHER ACTIVITIESIn 2015 she set up a grassroots training programme through her coach John Philip Duenas\' company JPD Coaching, to teach the fundamentals of running to children in Cebu, Philippines. (mycebu.ph, 20 Apr 2016; cebudailynews.inquirer.net, 19 Feb 2018)OTHER STUDIESShe has also studied for a master\'s degree in public administration at Southwestern University in Cebu, Philippines. (Facebook profile, 17 Apr 2018) '), ('Hero', 'Her coach John Philip Duenas. (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Influence', 'Her coach John Philip Duenas.
